  "description": "Frantz Fanon (1925-1961) was a Martinican psychiatrist, philosopher, and revolutionary whose analysis of the colonial subject's psychic formation and of the violence of decolonization is foundational to post-colonial thought, the black radical tradition, and the contemporary decolonial-critical apparatus.",
